## <a id="reqs"></a>Requirements

Heimdall Database Proxy for Pivotal Greenplum has the following requirements:

+ Java 8 or higher (When using Heimdall in a JDBC driver context, the application can run on Java 6+ if necessary)

+ 4 GB of RAM for a minimum install with caching

+ Pivotal Greenplum (all supported versions) and/or Postgres version 9.0 or higher

## <a id="limitations"></a>Limitations

+ The features supported by the proxy are limited to those supported by the Postgres JDBC Driver, As the JDBC driver is used to provide connectivity to the back-end database.  Further documentation on this topic can be found at: https://jdbc.postgresql.org/.

+ In order to cache a result-set, it must fit into the local heap of the proxy.

